;; A1: DFA/α fractal similarity
(given task-a1-dfa-alpha-fractal-similarity)
(given no-deps-a1)

(meta task-a1-dfa-alpha-fractal-similarity
  (description "CLAIM: DFA/α implementation correctly computes fractal similarity via detrended fluctuation analysis on semantic velocity (inter-turn cosine distances), producing meaningful α exponents where α≈0.5=white noise, α≈1.0=pink noise, α>1.2=lock-in. VERIFY: Read /Users/m3untold/Code/EarthianLabs/semantic-climate-phase-space/src/core_metrics.py — focus on fractal_similarity_robust(), _calculate_alpha_single(), and calculate_all_metrics() (the semantic velocity computation). Also read test files in /Users/m3untold/Code/EarthianLabs/semantic-climate-phase-space/tests/. Check: 1) Is DFA implemented correctly — cumulative sum of mean-centred signal, non-overlapping segments, polynomial detrending, RMS fluctuation, log-log regression? 2) Is the input signal correct — inter-turn cosine distances (semantic velocity), NOT embedding norms? 3) Do the scale parameters (min_scale=4, max_scale_factor=0.25) produce a meaningful range for typical dialogue lengths (20-60 turns → 19-59 velocity samples)? 4) Does the bootstrap CI resample correctly (should resample time series, not iid)? 5) Does the log-log regression handle edge cases (zero fluctuations, insufficient scales)? 6) Is the interpretation correct — α≈0.5 white noise, α≈1.0 pink noise, α>1.2 lock-in? 7) What happens with exactly 20 turns (minimum viable)? Write finding to findings-a/01-dfa-alpha-fractal-similarity.md.")
  (acceptance "1. Finding written to findings-a/01-dfa-alpha-fractal-similarity.md using Phase A output format from CLAUDE.md. 2. Evidence includes file paths and line numbers. 3. Verdict: CONFIRMED, PARTIAL, NOT CONFIRMED, or CONCERN.")
  (phase "A"))

(normally r-ready-a1 (and task-a1-dfa-alpha-fractal-similarity no-deps-a1) ready-a1)
(normally r-assign-a1 (and ready-a1 agent-claude-available) assign-to-a1-claude)

;; A2: Δκ semantic curvature
(given task-a2-delta-kappa-semantic-curvature)
(given no-deps-a2)

(meta task-a2-delta-kappa-semantic-curvature
  (description "CLAIM: Δκ (semantic curvature) correctly computes local trajectory curvature via discrete Frenet-Serret formula κ(t)=||a_perp||/||v||², independent of start/end points. VERIFY: Read /Users/m3untold/Code/EarthianLabs/semantic-climate-phase-space/src/core_metrics.py — focus on semantic_curvature_enhanced(), _compute_local_curvatures(), _calculate_curvature_single(). Also read test files in /Users/m3untold/Code/EarthianLabs/semantic-climate-phase-space/tests/. Check: 1) Is the Frenet-Serret formula correctly implemented — velocity as first difference, acceleration as second difference, a_perp via projection, κ=||a_perp||/||v||²? 2) Is the formula correct for high-dimensional spaces (cross product not defined, perpendicular projection used instead)? 3) Does the implementation handle degenerate cases — zero velocity, collinear trajectory, duplicate embeddings? 4) Is the bootstrap CI for curvature valid — sorting resampled indices preserves temporal order but creates gaps/duplicates? 5) Is the permutation test for significance appropriate — shuffled trajectory as null hypothesis? 6) Does mean local curvature correctly summarise trajectory bending? 7) Is the threshold 0.35 reasonable for semantic embedding trajectories? Write finding to findings-a/02-delta-kappa-semantic-curvature.md.")
  (acceptance "1. Finding written to findings-a/02-delta-kappa-semantic-curvature.md using Phase A output format from CLAUDE.md. 2. Evidence includes file paths and line numbers. 3. Verdict: CONFIRMED, PARTIAL, NOT CONFIRMED, or CONCERN.")
  (phase "A"))

(normally r-ready-a2 (and task-a2-delta-kappa-semantic-curvature no-deps-a2) ready-a2)
(normally r-assign-a2 (and ready-a2 agent-claude-available) assign-to-a2-claude)

;; A3: ΔH entropy shift JSD
(given task-a3-delta-h-entropy-shift-jsd)
(given no-deps-a3)

(meta task-a3-delta-h-entropy-shift-jsd
  (description "CLAIM: ΔH (entropy shift) correctly computes semantic reorganization via Jensen-Shannon divergence on shared clustering of pre/post embeddings, bounded [0,1]. VERIFY: Read /Users/m3untold/Code/EarthianLabs/semantic-climate-phase-space/src/core_metrics.py — focus on entropy_shift_comprehensive(), compute_js_divergence(), calculate_distributions_shared(). Also read test files in /Users/m3untold/Code/EarthianLabs/semantic-climate-phase-space/tests/. Check: 1) Is JSD correctly implemented — M=(P+Q)/2, JSD=0.5*KL(P||M)+0.5*KL(Q||M), using log base 2 for [0,1] bound? 2) Is shared clustering correct — fit on full trajectory, split labels to pre/post, compute distributions over all cluster IDs? 3) Does consensus across methods (kmeans+gmm) and cluster counts (6,8,10) add robustness or noise? 4) Does the stability_score (1 - std/mean) accurately reflect consensus? 5) Is the bootstrap CI valid — resampling pre and post independently, then re-clustering? 6) Does the epsilon (1e-12) for numerical stability affect the JSD bound? 7) What happens when pre and post have very different sizes or when embeddings are near-identical? Write finding to findings-a/03-delta-h-entropy-shift-jsd.md.")
  (acceptance "1. Finding written to findings-a/03-delta-h-entropy-shift-jsd.md using Phase A output format from CLAUDE.md. 2. Evidence includes file paths and line numbers. 3. Verdict: CONFIRMED, PARTIAL, NOT CONFIRMED, or CONCERN.")
  (phase "A"))

(normally r-ready-a3 (and task-a3-delta-h-entropy-shift-jsd no-deps-a3) ready-a3)
